---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { SOCIAL, daysFree } from '../lib/site';
import portrait from '../assets/brett-mount-lemmon.webp';
const days = daysFree();
---

<Base title="About" description="What RC Journey is, and the person behind it.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 pt-20 md:px-8">
    <PageHeader title="A travelogue with a purpose.">
      <Fragment slot="eyebrow">About · Day <span data-days-free>{days.toLocaleString('en-US')}</span> of freedom</Fragment>
    </PageHeader>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-12 md:px-8">
    <div class="prose-rcj">
      <p>
        The “RC” in RC Journey stands for <strong>Returning Citizen</strong> — someone
        transitioning back into society after a period of incarceration. This is a space
        where the breathtaking beauty of the American West is held up against the honest,
        often unseen, realities of reentry.
      </p>

      <Image src={portrait} alt="Brett on Mount Lemmon" widths={[640, 960]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" class="rounded-md" />

      <h2>What RC Journey is</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>A travelogue with a purpose.</strong> Cross-country travels through America’s
          landscapes — serene forests to majestic mountains — as a backdrop for reflection on
          resilience and the ongoing path of reentry.</li>
        <li><strong>A mirror to reentry realities.</strong> The systemic barriers and personal
          struggles returning citizens face daily: housing, employment, rebuilding relationships.</li>
        <li><strong>A platform for voices of resilience.</strong> Other returning citizens who have
          navigated reentry, in their own words.</li>
        <li><strong>A personal narrative.</strong> My own road from incarceration to a career as a
          Platform Systems Engineer at
          <a href="https://thelastmile.org">The Last Mile</a> — and now, traveler and storyteller.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Meet Brett</h2>
      <p>
        My name is Brett. After 24 years of incarceration, I committed to a path of personal and
        professional growth. My role as a Platform Systems Engineer isn’t just a job — it’s a
        testament to skill development, mentorship, and second chances. Remote work gives me the
        flexibility to merge a passion for technology and travel with a commitment to the reentry
        community.
      </p>

      <h2>The mission</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Humanize reentry</strong> through authentic stories that break down stigma.</li>
        <li><strong>Inspire hope</strong> through narratives of successful reentry and the beauty of nature.</li>
        <li><strong>Educate and inform</strong> about the challenges of reentry and what helps.</li>
        <li><strong>Build community</strong> for returning citizens, their loved ones, and advocates.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <hr class="horizon mt-12" />
    <p class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      {SOCIAL.map((s) => (
        <a href={s.href} rel="me noopener" class="rounded-full border border-line px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest no-underline hover:border-ochre">{s.label}</a>
      ))}
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
